    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-23T10:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-23T10:50:00-05:00" n="1326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1326">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.56374/4–2354: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1326<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-23T10:50:00-05:00"
                            >April 23, 1954—10:50 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1310. Noforn. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> conveyed
                    to Department through third party following comments from <persName
                        corresp="#p_NCGA1">Nasir</persName> on new British Suez Base proposals:</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Iran should not be mentioned in section providing for consultation in case
                        of threat of attack. Some general geographic expression could be used
                        instead.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>US should not be mentioned in describing consultations to be held in case
                        of threat of attack. Clause could state simply consultations will be held
                        without specifying between whom.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Participation of US firms in future operation and maintenance of Base
                        should not be mentioned.</item>
                </list>
                <p>We have not provided <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> with any
                    information on British proposals, but he appears quite well informed as to their
                    nature.</p>
                <p>Believe we should leave it to Egyptians to make above points to British when they
                    begin discussions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
